"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599517","Department of Health","false","2016-10-19","<p>The National Institute for Health and Care Excellence and NHS England launched a joint consultation on 13 October 2016 setting out proposed changes to the arrangements for the evaluation and adoption of new technologies, including on the methodology for the evaluation of highly specialised technologies.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood",,"2016-10-19T15:06:45.947Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599517/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599517/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599517/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-10-11","Medical Treatments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what plans (a) NICE and (b) NHS England has to issue a consultation on changes to the highly specialised technologies evaluation programme.","false","Biography information for John Glen","Salisbury","John Glen","47935"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599520","Department of Health","false","2016-10-19","<p>We want a clinically focussed community pharmacy service that is better integrated with primary care and public health in line with the Five Year Forward View. This will help relieve the pressure on general practitioners and accident and emergency, ensure better use of medicines and better patient outcomes, and contribute to delivering seven-day health and care services.</p><p>The Chief Pharmaceutical Officer for England, Dr Keith Ridge has commissioned an independent review of community pharmacy clinical services. The review is being led by Richard Murray, Director of Policy at The King’s Fund. The final recommendations will be considered as part of the development of clinical and cost effective patient care by pharmacists and their teams.</p><p>NHS England is also setting up a Pharmacy Integration Fund to support the development of clinical pharmacy practice in a wider range of primary care settings, resulting in a more integrated and effective National Health Service primary care patient pathway.</p>","Warrington South","David Mowat",,"2016-10-19T14:48:26.27Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599520/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599520/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599520/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-10-11","Pharmacy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what assessment he has made of the potential for community pharmacies to (a) deliver early identification of medical complaints and ongoing patient monitoring and (b) help reduce hospital admission rates.","false","Biography information for Nigel Adams","Selby and Ainsty","Nigel Adams","47927"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599521","Department of Health","false","2016-10-17","<p>The information requested is not centrally held and is a matter for the local National Health Service consortium which submitted the tender in question.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2016-10-17T16:23:13.22Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599521/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599521/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599521/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-10-11","Musculoskeletal Disorders: Greenwich","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what the cost to local NHS consortium formed of Lewisham and Greenwich Healthcare Trust, Local Care Networks and Oxleas Trust was of preparing their unsuccessful tender for the contract to provide musculoskeletal services in Greenwich; and if he will assess the effect of such spending on resources available for services to patients; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Clive Efford","Eltham","Clive Efford","48024"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599522","Department of Health","false","2016-10-17","<p>We are advised by NHS England that patients already on the waiting list for orthopaedic surgery will continue on their pathway as planned as at 1 December 2016.</p><p> </p><p>We are further advised by NHS England that Circle Health as the prime provider will liaise with the providers in question to change the pathway or expedite admission where clinical need arises.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2016-10-17T16:38:24.297Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599522/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599522/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599522/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-10-11","Circle","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what the implications are for patients who remain on the waiting list for orthopaedic surgery on 1 December 2016 of Circle Holdings PLC being awarded the contract for musculoskeletal services in Greenwich; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Clive Efford","Eltham","Clive Efford","48025"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599523","Department of Health","false","2016-10-17","<p>The number of National Health Service prescription charge penalty charge notices issued between September 2015 and August 2016, which is the most recent 12-month period for which we have complete data, was 780,953. Where no response was received to the initial penalty charge notice a follow up surcharge letter was issued to the patient. For the same period a total of 333,508 surcharge letters were issued.</p><p>The value of the recovered prescription income in this period was £2,556,941, and the value of the income from penalty charges and surcharges was £8,678,911 and £745,830, respectively.</p><p>Since taking over the administration of the Prescription Exemption Checking Service in September 2014, the NHS Business Services Authority has not issued any court proceedings for debt recovery in relation to NHS prescription charges and penalties.</p>","Warrington South","David Mowat","48027","2016-10-17T15:25:36.037Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599523/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599523/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599523/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-10-11","Prescriptions: Fees and Charges","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many NHS prescription charge penalty charge notices were issued in the last year for which figures are available; and how much was recovered in (a) prescription income and (b) penalty charges and surcharges in the last year for which information is available.","false","Biography information for Sir Christopher Chope","Christchurch","Mr Christopher Chope","48026"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599524","Department of Health","false","2016-10-17","<p>The provision of local health services is a matter for the local National Health Service.</p><p> </p><p>There have been no meetings between Ministers at the Department of Health and Greenwich Clinical Commissioning Group (CCG) about the award of the contract to provide musculoskeletal services to Circle Holdings PLC regarding the Sustainability and Transformation Plans for elective orthopaedic surgery in Greenwich.</p><p> </p><p>Neither have there been meetings between Ministers at the Department and Greenwich CCG regarding the capacity of local health providers meeting the <em>Getting it Right First Time</em> requirements in Greenwich since the contract to provide musculoskeletal services was awarded to Circle Holdings PLC.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","48023","2016-10-17T16:21:37.033Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599524/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599524/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599524/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-10-11","Circle","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what discussions he has had with Greenwich Clinical Commissioning Group on the capacity of local health providers meeting the Getting it Right First Time requirements in Greenwich since the contract to provide musculoskeletal services was awarded to Circle Holdings PLC; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Clive Efford","Eltham","Clive Efford","48022"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599526","Department of Health","false","2016-10-18","<p>Since entering Special Measures in November 2015, the London Ambulance Service has reduced the gap from 3% behind the national average for Category A Red 1 Calls 8 minute standard, to 1.3% in August 2016, and is consistently above the national average for the remaining Category A Red 1 and 2 performance standards.</p><p>The London Ambulance Service has met its A8 performance recovery trajectory each month from April to August 2016 in spite of growth in incidents of 5.4% above the original contract plan.</p><p>South East Coast Ambulance Service entered Special Measures in September 2016 and is now receiving a comprehensive package of support, including buddying with South Central Ambulance Service and an Improvement Director has been appointed.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2016-10-18T10:43:49.97Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599526/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599526/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599526/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-10-11","Ambulance Services: Standards","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what progress his Department has made on improving the performance of ambulance services which are in special measures.","false","Biography information for Rehman Chishti","Gillingham and Rainham","Rehman Chishti","48018"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599527","Department of Health","false","2016-10-17","<p>The number of National Health Service prescription charge penalty charge notices issued between September 2015 and August 2016, which is the most recent 12-month period for which we have complete data, was 780,953. Where no response was received to the initial penalty charge notice a follow up surcharge letter was issued to the patient. For the same period a total of 333,508 surcharge letters were issued.</p><p>The value of the recovered prescription income in this period was £2,556,941, and the value of the income from penalty charges and surcharges was £8,678,911 and £745,830, respectively.</p><p>Since taking over the administration of the Prescription Exemption Checking Service in September 2014, the NHS Business Services Authority has not issued any court proceedings for debt recovery in relation to NHS prescription charges and penalties.</p>","Warrington South","David Mowat","48026","2016-10-17T15:25:36.097Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599527/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599527/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599527/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-10-11","Prescriptions: Fees and Charges","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many proceedings for debt recovery the NHS has issued in the county court for NHS prescription charges and penalties in the last year for which information is available; how many such proceedings resulted in recovery of the outstanding money.","false","Biography information for Sir Christopher Chope","Christchurch","Mr Christopher Chope","48027"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599528","Department of Health","false","2016-10-17","<p>The provision of local health services is a matter for the local National Health Service.</p><p> </p><p>There have been no meetings between Ministers at the Department of Health and Greenwich Clinical Commissioning Group (CCG) about the award of the contract to provide musculoskeletal services to Circle Holdings PLC regarding the Sustainability and Transformation Plans for elective orthopaedic surgery in Greenwich.</p><p> </p><p>Neither have there been meetings between Ministers at the Department and Greenwich CCG regarding the capacity of local health providers meeting the <em>Getting it Right First Time</em> requirements in Greenwich since the contract to provide musculoskeletal services was awarded to Circle Holdings PLC.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","48022","2016-10-17T16:21:36.97Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599528/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599528/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599528/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-10-11","Circle","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what discussions he has had with Greenwich Clinical Commissioning Group since the award of the contract to provide musculoskeletal services to Circle Holdings PLC on the Sustainability and Transformation Plans for elective orthopaedic surgery in Greenwich; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Clive Efford","Eltham","Clive Efford","48023"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599529","Department of Health","false","2016-10-19","<p>Patient and Public Involvement (PPI) is enshrined in S.242 of the National Health Service Act 2006. The Health and Social Care Act 2012 amended S.242 and included complementary duties for clinical commissioning groups (CCGs) and NHS England.</p><p>Since the 2012 Act NHS England has published statutory guidance for NHS commissioners and revised guidance for CCGs will be published in spring 2017. A further guide on engaging communities, for areas developing Sustainability and Transformation Plans, was published by NHS England in September 2016. NHS England has also recently launched an Involvement Hub, an online resource to support patients, carers, staff and the public, which also includes examples of good practice and links to learning and involvement opportunities.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2016-10-19T10:10:03.21Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599529/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599529/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599529/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-10-11","NHS: Public Participation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what steps he has taken to improve public and patient involvement in the NHS.","false","Biography information for Mr Geoffrey Cox","Torridge and West Devon","Mr Geoffrey Cox","47968"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599531","Department of Health","false","2016-10-19","<p>The National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE) is currently evaluating the costs and benefits of asfotase alfa (Strensiq) for treating paediatric-onset hypophosphatasia to determine whether it can be recommended for national commissioning by NHS England.</p><p>There has not yet been an opportunity for stakeholders to appeal NICE’s recommendations on the use of asfotase alfa for treating paediatric-onset hypophosphatasia. NICE published a second iteration of draft guidance for consultation on 22 September 2016 and the closing date for comments was 13 October 2016. NICE’s independent Evaluation Committee will now consider the comments received in response to the consultation before deciding on the next steps for the evaluation.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood","47970","2016-10-19T15:05:07.607Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599531/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599531/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599531/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-10-11","Asfotase Alfa","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, whether he plans to appeal NICE's draft guidance on asfotase alfa for treating paediatric-onset hypophosphatasia, issued in September 2016.","false","Biography information for John Glen","Salisbury","John Glen","47969"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599532","Department of Health","false","2016-10-19","<p>The National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE) is currently evaluating the costs and benefits of asfotase alfa (Strensiq) for treating paediatric-onset hypophosphatasia to determine whether it can be recommended for national commissioning by NHS England.</p><p>There has not yet been an opportunity for stakeholders to appeal NICE’s recommendations on the use of asfotase alfa for treating paediatric-onset hypophosphatasia. NICE published a second iteration of draft guidance for consultation on 22 September 2016 and the closing date for comments was 13 October 2016. NICE’s independent Evaluation Committee will now consider the comments received in response to the consultation before deciding on the next steps for the evaluation.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood","47969","2016-10-19T15:05:07.667Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599532/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599532/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599532/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-10-11","Asfotase Alfa","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what steps his Department is taking to ensure that asfotase alfa is available on the NHS to all patients who may benefit from it.","false","Biography information for John Glen","Salisbury","John Glen","47970"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599533","Department of Health","false","2016-10-19","<p>Prone restraint data for years since 2012 is not available. NHS Digital began collecting the number of incidents of prone restraint on mental health wards for adults and for children and young people in January 2016. In line with the UK Statistics Authority’s Code of Practice, this data is undergoing evaluation.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood","47972","2016-10-19T15:54:46.747Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599533/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599533/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599533/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-10-11","Mental Patients: Restraint Techniques","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many instances were recorded in which a young person was restrained physically by placing their face on the floor in a children's mental health ward in each year from 2012.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","47971"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599534","Department of Health","false","2016-10-19","<p>Prone restraint data for years since 2012 is not available. NHS Digital began collecting the number of incidents of prone restraint on mental health wards for adults and for children and young people in January 2016. In line with the UK Statistics Authority’s Code of Practice, this data is undergoing evaluation.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood","47971","2016-10-19T15:54:46.687Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599534/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599534/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599534/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-10-11","Mental Patients: Restraint Techniques","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many instances were recorded in which a person was restrained physically by placing their face on the floor in a mental health ward in each year from 2012.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","47972"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599535","Department of Health","false","2016-10-17","<p>Department of Health ministers have had no recent meetings or discussions with representatives from Gloucestershire Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust regarding its financial deficit over the last six months.</p><p> </p><p>On 17 October 2016 NHS Improvement announced Gloucestershire Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust has entered Financial Special Measures.</p><p> </p><p>The Financial Special Measures programme launched by NHS Improvement provides a rapid turnaround package for trusts and foundation trusts which have either not agreed savings targets (also known as control totals) with local commissioners, or planned to make savings but deviated significantly from this plan.</p><p> </p><p>As part of financial special measures, each trust agrees a recovery plan with NHS Improvement. The trusts also get support from – and are held accountable by – a Financial Improvement Director appointed by NHS Improvement.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2016-10-17T16:57:09.807Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599535/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599535/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599535/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-10-11","Gloucestershire Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what recent discussions he has had with representatives of the Gloucestershire Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust on the financial deficit of that Trust.","false","Biography information for Mr Laurence Robertson","Tewkesbury","Mr Laurence Robertson","47996"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599537","Department of Health","false","2016-10-17","<p><em>Crohn’s Disease Management in Adults, Children and Young People</em>, published by the National Institute for Health and Care Excellence in October 2012, sets out best practice guidance for clinicians and commissioners in the diagnosis, treatment care and support of patients with Crohn’s disease. The guidance includes a number of specific recommendations concerning young people such as the need to offer age-appropriate multidisciplinary support to deal with any concerns about the disease and its treatment, including concerns about body image, living with a chronic illness, and attending school and higher education.</p>","Warrington South","David Mowat",,"2016-10-17T16:00:34.167Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599537/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599537/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599537/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-10-11","Crohn's Disease: Health Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what support his Department makes available for young people diagnosed with Crohn's disease.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","48000"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599538","Department of Health","false","2016-10-17","<p>My Rt. hon. Friend the Secretary of State has not had discussions with Ministers in the devolved administrations on fully funded NHS Continuing Healthcare.</p>","Warrington South","David Mowat",,"2016-10-17T16:07:24.627Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599538/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599538/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599538/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-10-11","Continuing Care: Devolution","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what discussions he has had with Ministers in the devolved administrations on fully funded NHS Continuing Healthcare.","false","Biography information for Baroness Ritchie of Downpatrick","South Down","Ms Margaret Ritchie","48005"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599539","Department of Health","true","2016-10-17","<p>The procurement of local health services by means of competitive tendering is a matter for the local National Health Service.</p><p> </p><p>We are advised by NHS England that Greenwich Clinical Commissioning Group’s Turnaround Director and Musculoskeletal (MSK) Programme Manager met the senior management team of Lewisham and Greenwich Healthcare Trust in March 2016. We understand that the implications of the MSK service procurement were discussed in detail, and that there were no concerns with regard to the viability of any other services the Trust provides.</p><p> </p><p>We are further advised by NHS England that it undertook an assurance of the procurement process for the MSK service in Greenwich in August 2016<ins class="ministerial">. We also understand that NHS Improvement was aware of the procurement and briefly discussed it with the Trust during a standing monthly meeting on 21 June 2016. </ins> <del class="ministerial">and as part of this also met with the Trust to discuss the implications of the procurement for the trust.</del></p><p>We understand that Circle Health has been engaging with Lewisham and Greenwich Healthcare Trust as part of the mobilisation process, including developing clinical and operational delivery plans to provide integrated services.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2016-10-17T16:19:10.383Z","2016-11-17T14:14:49.887Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599539/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599539/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599539/answer","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599539/answer/previousversion/14633","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","17","Health","Health","2016-10-11","Circle","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what assessment his Department has made of the potential effect of decisions taken by Circle Holdings PLC in the delivery of musculoskeletal services in Greenwich on the financial capacity of the local healthcare trust to sustain accident and emergency services at University Hospital Lewisham and Queen Elizabeth Hospital Woolwich; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Clive Efford","Eltham","Clive Efford","48002"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599540","Department of Health","false","2016-10-19","<p>The provision of local health services is a matter for the local National Health Service.</p><p> </p><p>There have been no meetings between Ministers at the Department of Health and Greenwich Clinical Commissioning Group (CCG) on progress towards meeting the Getting it Right First Time requirements since the contract for musculoskeletal services was awarded to Circle Holdings PLC.</p><p> </p><p>Neither have there been meetings between Ministers at the Department and Greenwich CCG regarding the future of the Fracture Clinic Service and physiotherapy service in Greenwich and on whether the service is included in the contract awarded to Circle Holdings PLC to provide musculoskeletal services.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","48012","2016-10-19T10:57:58.57Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599540/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599540/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599540/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-10-11","Circle","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what discussions he has had with Greenwich Clinical Commissioning Group on the future of the Fracture Clinic Service and physiotherapy service in Greenwich and whether that service is included in the contract awarded to Circle Holdings PLC to provide musculoskeletal services; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Clive Efford","Eltham","Clive Efford","48011"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599542","Department of Health","false","2016-10-19","<p>The provision of local health services is a matter for the local National Health Service.</p><p> </p><p>There have been no meetings between Ministers at the Department of Health and Greenwich Clinical Commissioning Group (CCG) on progress towards meeting the Getting it Right First Time requirements since the contract for musculoskeletal services was awarded to Circle Holdings PLC.</p><p> </p><p>Neither have there been meetings between Ministers at the Department and Greenwich CCG regarding the future of the Fracture Clinic Service and physiotherapy service in Greenwich and on whether the service is included in the contract awarded to Circle Holdings PLC to provide musculoskeletal services.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne","48011","2016-10-19T10:57:58.507Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599542/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599542/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599542/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-10-11","Circle","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what discussions he has had with Lewisham and Greenwich Healthcare Trust on progress towards meeting the Getting it Right First Time requirements since the contract for musculoskeletal services was awarded to Circle Holdings PLC; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Clive Efford","Eltham","Clive Efford","48012"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599543","Department of Health","false","2016-10-19","<p>Employers across the National Health Service are responsible for the health and wellbeing of all their staff. They will provide access to a range of services and support to staff including doctors who feel they are experiencing stress.</p><p> </p><p>The Department continues to commission NHS Employers to provide advice, guidance and good practice to the NHS on improving staff physical and mental health and wellbeing. This includes an emotional wellbeing toolkit enabling staff to check their own emotional wellbeing and encourage discussion with colleagues. NHS Employers is also working with NHS England who are investing £5 million in a new NHS staff physical and mental health and wellbeing initiative, with the support of Public Health England.</p><p> </p><p>There are particular additional issues for junior doctors relating to the need for them to move between different hospitals in the course of their training. Health Education England, which is responsible for doctor training arrangements has a programme of work to address these issues. This includes looking at reducing the number of training rotations to help balance doctors’ work and other responsibilities such as family and caring commitments, giving doctors ten weeks’ notice of new placements and reviewing the process for the annual review of competence progression to reduce unnecessary bureaucracy.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2016-10-19T15:45:51.397Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599543/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599543/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599543/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-10-11","Health Professions: Stress","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, if he will take steps to provide support for (a) junior doctors and (b) other medical staff employed in hospitals who are experiencing stress.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","48109"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599544","Department of Health","false","2016-10-19","<p>As part of the second devolution deal agreed with Liverpool City Region in March 2016, the Government committed to ongoing dialogue with the city region with regards to their health and social care system. The Government welcomes the publication of Liverpool City Region’s Case for Change which clearly set out the challenges faced by that health system and which necessitates a collective focus on prevention and early intervention. The Department and national partners continue to engage with Liverpool City Region with regards to next steps.</p>","Warrington South","David Mowat",,"2016-10-19T14:55:05.73Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599544/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599544/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/599544/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2016-10-11","Health Services: Liverpool City Region","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what recent discussions he has held on the devolution of health services in the Liverpool City Region.","false","Biography information for Sir George Howarth","Knowsley","Mr George Howarth","48190"
