"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598169","Cabinet Office","false","2016-10-13","<p>Between November 2005 and May 2006 the role of the Chancellor was vacant. During that period the Duchy was administered by the Chief Executive and Clerk of the Council, along with the Duchy Council.</p><p>Since I have taken up the role, I have been carrying out a number of duties related to the Duchy, including meetings with Duchy staff, a visit to a Duchy property and various appointments and responsibilities associated with the office.</p>","Derbyshire Dales","Sir Patrick McLoughlin","47894","2016-10-13T12:34:26.477Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598169/answer","Biography information for Sir Patrick McLoughlin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598169/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598169/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-10-10","Duchy of Lancaster","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, if he will estimate the proportion of time Ministers in his Department spent on the management of matters relating to the Duchy of Lancaster in the last three months.","false","Biography information for Tommy Sheppard","Edinburgh East","Tommy Sheppard","47683"
