"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598176","HM Treasury","false","2016-10-14","<p>The Government noted the report with interest and is grateful for the important work that The Children’s Society does. The Government is committed to supporting individuals in problem debt.</p><p> </p><p>The Government is exploring whether some form of “breathing space” would be a useful and viable addition to the range of formal and informal debt solutions available to consumers and creditors. Officials in HM Treasury and the Insolvency Service have been asked to discuss this issue with stakeholders and the Government will report back this autumn.</p>","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby","47829","2016-10-14T09:55:15.25Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598176/answer","Biography information for Simon Kirby","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598176/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598176/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-10-10","Debts","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what steps his Department is taking to protect families paying debts over time from bailiff fees, court charges and interest rates; and if he will consider a statutory breathing space for families in debt.","false","Biography information for Helen Goodman","Bishop Auckland","Helen Goodman","47723"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598177","HM Treasury","false","2016-10-13","<p>The Chancellor announced that the Treasury will provide a guarantee for all new structural and investment fund projects, signed after Autumn Statement, and before we leave the EU, where they provide value for money and support domestic strategic priorities.</p><p> </p><p>Each government department will take responsibility for the allocation of money to projects in line with these conditions and the wider rules on public spending. The Treasury will work with departments to embed this approach.</p><p> </p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2016-10-13T14:10:47.577Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598177/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598177/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598177/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-10-10","EU Grants and Loans","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, with reference to his announcement on EU regional funding dated 3 October 2016, what conditions will need to be passed by funding projects to ensure they are (i) good value for money and (ii) in line with domestic strategic priorities; and if he will guarantee that all regions will receive the full amount of funding they were allocated by the EU.","false","Biography information for Tim Farron","Westmorland and Lonsdale","Tim Farron","47657"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598178","HM Treasury","false","2016-10-13","Concentrix’s workload is delegated by HM Revenue and Customs. Using postcode areas for selection criteria is outside the scope of Concentrix. Information about the use of profiling techniques can be found in section A10.1 of the Concentrix contract at: <a href="https://www.contractsfinder.service.gov.uk/Notice/85d1b730-5e4e-4be8-ae4c-3ac1f359afc7" target="_blank">https://www.contractsfinder.service.gov.uk/Notice/85d1b730-5e4e-4be8-ae4c-3ac1f359afc7</a>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2016-10-13T16:16:03.437Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598178/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598178/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598178/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-10-10","Concentrix","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether he has received any reports that Concentrix has used postcode areas to target tax credit claimants with allegations that they have provided incorrect claim information.","false","Biography information for Helen Goodman","Bishop Auckland","Helen Goodman","47652"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598179","HM Treasury","false","2016-10-14","<p>The Government noted the report with interest and is grateful for the important work that The Children’s Society does. The Government is committed to supporting individuals in problem debt.</p><p> </p><p>The Government is exploring whether some form of “breathing space” would be a useful and viable addition to the range of formal and informal debt solutions available to consumers and creditors. Officials in HM Treasury and the Insolvency Service have been asked to discuss this issue with stakeholders and the Government will report back this autumn.</p>","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby","47723","2016-10-14T09:55:15.187Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598179/answer","Biography information for Simon Kirby","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598179/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598179/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2016-10-10","Debts","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment he has made of the implication for his Department's policies of the Children's Society's recent report, Damage of Debt; and if his Department will introduce a statutory breathing space scheme for families in debt.","false","Biography information for Helen Goodman","Bishop Auckland","Helen Goodman","47829"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598180","Church Commissioners","false","2016-10-13","<p>The Church Commissioners have made an emergency loan to help address the cashflow challenges at Peterbourough Cathedral. In addition to this financial assistance, they have also actively supported and continue to support the Cathedral and Chapter by giving practical assistance, for example helping the Chapter evaluate options for staff restructuring and its property sale programme.</p><p> </p><p>The Bishop of Peterborough has launched a visitation which will include a review of financial management and overall governance of the cathedral. The Commissioners are assisting in this process and I am happy to say that governance is improving and Chapter is beginning to address its budget deficit.</p><p> </p>","Meriden","Dame Caroline Spelman",,"2016-10-13T11:17:42.34Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598180/answer","Biography information for Dame Caroline Spelman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598180/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598180/answer",,,,,"9","Church Commissioners","Church Commissioners","2016-10-10","Peterborough Cathedral: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the right hon. Member for Meriden, representing the Church Commissioners, what steps are being taken by the Church Commissioners to address the financial difficulties at Peterborough Cathedral; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mr Stewart Jackson","Peterborough","Mr Stewart Jackson","47672"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598181","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-10-18","<p>The Future High Street Forum was set up to provide joint business and government leadership to better enable our high streets and town centres to adapt and compete in the face of changing consumer and social trends. It advises the government in the formation and delivery of policies to support high streets and town centres and comprises a wide range of organisations that are involved in the high street.</p><p>The Forum’s Executive Board has met 6 times in the past two years, including three times in 2016 so far.</p>","Brigg and Goole","Andrew Percy",,"2016-10-18T15:16:59.187Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598181/answer","Biography information for Andrew Percy","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598181/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598181/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-10-10","Future High Streets Forum","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, when the future high streets forum has met in the last two years; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Gareth Thomas","Harrow West","Gareth Thomas","47834"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598182","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-11-10","<p>The Department is not able to confirm the total number of letters received by the Department from the Mayor of London since 2010 as this would incur disproportionate cost.</p>","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones",,"2016-11-10T17:19:57.077Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598182/answer","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598182/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598182/answer","Nuneaton","Mr Marcus Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598182/answer/previousversion/15114","Biography information for Mr Marcus Jones","7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2016-10-10","Department for Communities and Local Government: Mayor of London","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, how many letters his Department received from the Mayor of London between May 2010 and April 2016; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Gareth Thomas","Harrow West","Gareth Thomas","47835"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598183","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-10-18","<p>Ofcom is the regulator with responsibility for on-demand programme services (ODPS). Ofcom are presently consulting on how to improve access services.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2016-10-18T09:07:04.633Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598183/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598183/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598183/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-10-10","Video on Demand","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what steps she will take to ensure that people with audio or visual impairments benefit from the Digital Economy Bill; and if she will assess how on-demand services will meet such people's needs.","false","Biography information for Neil Coyle","Bermondsey and Old Southwark","Neil Coyle","47847"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598184","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-10-18","<p>I refer my honourable friend to the answer to PQ 47854.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2016-10-18T09:05:21.847Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598184/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598184/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598184/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-10-10","Infant Foods","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, if she will issue a response to the report Scientific and factual? A review of breastmilk substitute advertising to healthcare professionals, published by the First Steps Nutrition Trust.","false","Biography information for Alison Thewliss","Glasgow Central","Alison Thewliss","47844"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598185","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-10-17","<p>The Secretary of State and I are currently considering s.40 of the Crime and Courts Act 2013 and we are meeting interested parties as part of these considerations.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2016-10-17T14:24:40.407Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598185/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598185/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598185/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-10-10","Mass Media: Legal Costs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what assessment she has made of the effect of bringing into force the costs sanctions under section 40 of the Crime and Courts Act 2013 on individual press titles that have joined the Independent Press Standards Organisation.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","47763"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598186","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-10-13","<p>Sport England’s latest Active People Survey results show that the number of women playing sport and being active in England is fast increasing, with over 7 million females aged 16 years or over playing sport once a week - an increase of 261,200 since March 2015.</p><p> </p><p>However, we recognise that there are various obstacles which still exist that put women off sport and initiatives such as This Girl Can, a Sport England behaviour change campaign, have helped encourage women and girls to get active. In addition the Government’s strategy for sport and physical activity ‘Sporting Future: A New Strategy for An Active Nation’ and Sport England’s strategy ‘Towards an Active Nation’ aim to create a more physically active nation, where people of all ages and backgrounds can enjoy the benefits that sport and physical activity can provide. Both also put a strong emphasis on reaching groups that are under-represented in sport and physical activity, including women and girls, and helping them to get active in ways that suit them.</p><p> </p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"2016-10-13T09:22:43.7Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598186/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598186/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598186/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-10-10","Sports: Females","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what steps her Department is taking to encourage female participation in sport.","false","Biography information for Julie Elliott","Sunderland Central","Julie Elliott","47668"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598187","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2016-10-18","<p>We recognise the importance of tackling childhood obesity, which is caused by a number of complex factors. The Childhood Obesity Plan for Action, published in August, considered a number of different policy responses to address this problem. Additional advertising restrictions were considered as part of this process, but current restrictions in the UK are amongst the toughest in the world and the plan focuses on those areas which experts tell us are most effective.</p>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock",,"2016-10-18T09:01:51.987Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598187/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598187/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598187/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2016-10-10","Advertising: Food","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, if she will make it her policy to restrict television advertising for unhealthy food on programming likely to be watched by children.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","47703"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598188","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-10-14","<p>The airfield at Leuchars Station does not routinely receive private aircraft. However, visiting aircraft can be parked, including overnight, on the aircraft servicing platforms by the side of the runway. This does not impede any military flying.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2016-10-14T12:16:40.433Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598188/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598188/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598188/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-10-10","RAF Leuchars","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what arrangements have been made to accommodate private aircraft at the Leuchars military base.","false","Biography information for Stephen Gethins","North East Fife","Stephen Gethins","47635"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598189","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-10-13","<p>The Armed Forces Covenant ensures that those who serve and have served in the Armed Forces, and their families, are treated fairly. In June 2013 the Chancellor announced that the financial commitment to the Armed Forces Covenant would be made permanent through a £10 million fund per annum in perpetuity from 2015-16.</p><p>The Annual Report on the Armed Forces Covenant from December 2015 detailed a number of achievements of which this Government can be proud, including allocating £40 million for accommodation projects for veterans; the £200 million Forces Help to Buy Scheme; and a world class centre for excellence for the training and delivery of Defence Medical Services.</p><p>In 2016 to date under the large grants scheme we have awarded a total of almost £7.5 million to 24 projects supporting community integration, criminal justice system initiatives and the co-ordination and delivery of support. Under the small grants scheme we have awarded a total of almost £2.4 million to 150 community integration projects. Depending on the quality of the bids, we hope to be able to announce the preferred bidder for the Veterans Gateway Service in November, as well as further tranches of Covenant Grant funding.</p><p>In January 2016, the Department published the first ever Armed Forces Families Strategy, embracing seven key themes - partner employment, accommodation, children's education and childcare, community support, specialist support, health and wellbeing, and transition. This is now routine business supporting our families.</p><p>We have reviewed our casualty and compassionate processes, and this autumn we are introducing a new reserves welfare health-check. In the last year Defence has enabled payroll deductions for Service personnel to take advantage of the savings and cheap loan facilities from selected credit unions. This facility was extended to veterans in receipt of a pension in March 2016.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2016-10-13T14:59:50.333Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598189/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598189/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598189/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-10-10","Armed Forces","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what steps he is taking to promote the welfare of members of the armed forces.","false","Biography information for Julie Elliott","Sunderland Central","Julie Elliott","47669"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598190","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-10-13","<p>Over the past 15 years, UK Armed Forces have provided support to armed forces of Gulf States both in-country and in the UK and continue to do so. Gulf States have attended international defence training courses in the UK such as the advanced command and staff course, Royal College of Defence Studies and Initial Officer Training.</p><p>UK Armed Forces have also provided training in-country through the delivery of tactical level Short Term Training Teams in the maritime, land and air domains. The Defence Academy has also delivered the strategic leadership programme and managing defence in wider security context courses to Gulf States along with the Royal Navy's exclusive economic zone course.</p><p> </p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2016-10-13T15:03:05.503Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598190/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598190/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598190/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-10-10","Gulf States: Military Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what involvement the UK armed forces have had in training armed forces of Gulf states in each of the last 15 years.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","47793"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598191","Cabinet Office","false","2016-10-19","<p>The Gulf Strategy Integrated Delivery Team was established in 2015.</p><p>Its remit is to coordinate the Government’s strategic approach to UK engagement with the Gulf States as set out in the Strategic Defence and Security Review 2015.</p><p>It employs three full-time and one part-time Government employees. One is military and three are civilian.</p><p>Administration costs were £70,004 in the 2015-16 financial year and the budget for administration costs in the 2016-17 financial year is £423,000. The 2015-16 figure reflects the fact the unit was established later in the financial year.</p>","Ipswich","Ben Gummer","47638 ; 47725 ; 47797","2016-10-19T11:17:58.527Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598191/answer","Biography information for Ben Gummer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598191/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598191/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-10-10","Gulf Strategy Unit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how much funding the Gulf Strategy Unit has received in each of the last 15 years.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","47796"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598192","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-10-17","<p>The P-8A Poseidon aircraft will form a vital part of the UK's maritime patrol capability, and interoperability with other platforms and systems is a key user requirement. Work to enable this is under way, however, I am withholding further detail as its disclosure would, or would be likely to prejudice the capability, effectiveness or security of the Armed Forces.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2016-10-17T14:28:57.517Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598192/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598192/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598192/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-10-10","Military Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what steps his Department is taking to ensure future interoperability of the Boeing Poseidon P-8 platform with the General Atomics MQ9 Reaper platforms.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","47717"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598193","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-10-17","<p>I am withholding information on the type of motors for the propulsion systems being considered for the Successor submarine programme for the purpose of safeguarding national security.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2016-10-17T14:32:37.9Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598193/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598193/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598193/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-10-10","Nuclear Submarines","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether his Department is considering (a) radial gap electrical propulsion motors and (b) permanent magnet motors for the propulsion systems for the successor-class SSBNs.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","47718"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598194","Cabinet Office","false","2016-10-19","<p>The Gulf Strategy Integrated Delivery Team was established in 2015.</p><p>Its remit is to coordinate the Government’s strategic approach to UK engagement with the Gulf States as set out in the Strategic Defence and Security Review 2015.</p><p>It employs three full-time and one part-time Government employees. One is military and three are civilian.</p><p>Administration costs were £70,004 in the 2015-16 financial year and the budget for administration costs in the 2016-17 financial year is £423,000. The 2015-16 figure reflects the fact the unit was established later in the financial year.</p>","Ipswich","Ben Gummer","47638 ; 47725 ; 47796","2016-10-19T11:17:58.59Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598194/answer","Biography information for Ben Gummer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598194/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598194/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-10-10","Gulf Strategy Unit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what the Gulf Strategy Unit's remit is; and which Government Minister set that remit.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","47797"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598195","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-10-17","<p>I am withholding the information as its disclosure would, or would be likely to prejudice the capability, effectiveness or security of the Armed Forces.</p><p>However, indiscriminate attacks which fail to distinguish between civilians and legitimate military targets would be a violation of International Humanitarian Law and we welcome the UN's recent decision to establish an Internal Board of Inquiry into the attack on a UN aid convoy on 19 September.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning","47537 ; 47538 ; 47539","2016-10-17T14:27:09.837Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598195/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598195/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598195/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-10-10","Syria: Armed Conflict","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether the Government has access to radar data covering Aleppo on 17 August 2016 that might identify the type, origin and identity of aircraft present for the air attack on the Qaterji neighbourhood on that day.","false","Biography information for Helen Hayes","Dulwich and West Norwood","Helen Hayes","47702"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598196","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-10-17","<p>There were four separate periods during July and August 2016 when all six Daring Class Type 45 Destroyers were alongside together at Her Majesty's Naval Base Portsmouth for consecutive days. These were for two days, two and a half days, four days, and twenty five and a half days.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2016-10-17T14:32:52.84Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598196/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598196/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598196/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-10-10","Type 45 Destroyers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 20 September 2016 to Question 45999, how many of the 34 days in which all six Daring-class Type 45 Destroyers were berthed together at HMNB Portsmouth were consecutive.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","47824"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598197","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-10-14","<p>The Ministry of Defence (MOD) routinely carries out checks on potential contractors prior to contract award, including on criminal activity, such as convictions for tax evasion, bribery or fraud, and a review of a company's audited accounts. These enquiries are conducted in accordance with the Public Contracts Regulations 2015 and the Defence and Security Public Contracts Regulations 2011.</p><p>This process is reiterated in all competitive and single source tender documentation issued to tenderers prior to any contract award.</p><p>Any suspicion of corruption is reported to the appropriate authority. Where justified, the MOD can exclude potential suppliers who pose an unacceptable risk to public money.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin","47532 ; 48114","2016-10-14T12:18:05.277Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598197/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598197/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598197/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-10-10","Ministry of Defence: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many times officials in his Department responsible for procurement checked whether a contractor employed by his Department was under investigation for corruption with law enforcement agencies in the last two years.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","47726"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598198","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2016-10-18","<p>We are supporting the Iraqi government in its efforts to unite Mosul's communities against Daesh and extremism, rebuild public trust in the Iraqi state and deliver the services and opportunities which all Maslawis want and deserve. Our goal is to liberate Mosul, in a way that protects civilians, minimises the humanitarian impact, and limits longer-term conflict by supporting political reconciliation.</p><p>The UK has pledged £9.25m to the UN's Funding Facility for Immediate Stabilisation, which is supporting the Iraqi government to stabilise areas recently liberated from Daesh and has so far helped 775,000 people return to their homes by re-establishing security, basic services and inclusive local governance. The Development Secretary announced a further £40 million in humanitarian assistance for Iraq at the UN General Assembly on 21 September, specifically to support the response to Mosul.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2016-10-18T14:01:52.87Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598198/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598198/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598198/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2016-10-10","Iraq: Military Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, how the UK is supporting the Iraqi government in its preparations to restore inclusive governance in Mosul after that city is removed from the control of IS.","false","Biography information for Brendan O'Hara","Argyll and Bute","Brendan O'Hara","47775"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598199","Department for International Development","false","2016-10-17","<p>On 21 September, the UK announced an extra £40 million of humanitarian funding to Iraq, taking our total commitment to £90 million this financial year and £169.5 million since June 2014. This new assistance will be targeted specifically to enable a scale up of humanitarian assistance ahead of the Government of Iraq-led Mosul operations. It will provide emergency life-saving assistance – such as food, shelter, medical and protection services – to civilians affected by Mosul operations, as well as continued support to displaced and vulnerable people across the country.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2016-10-17T16:31:54.503Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598199/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598199/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598199/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-10-10","Iraq: Armed Conflict","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what steps are being taken to attend to Iraqi civilians expected to be displaced as a result of a planned offensive on Mosul, Iraq.","false","Biography information for Brendan O'Hara","Argyll and Bute","Brendan O'Hara","47776"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598200","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-10-17","<table><tbody><tr><td colspan="2" rowspan="5"><p> </p></td><td colspan="6" rowspan="5"><p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer given by my hon. Friend the former Minister for Defence Procurement (Philip Dunne) on 1 July 2013 (Official Report, column 405W) to the right hon. Member for Moray (Angus Robertson).</p></td></tr></tbody></table>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2016-10-17T14:29:56.523Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598200/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598200/answer","Hansard Extract 1 July 2013 HOC162999.docx","Hansard Extract 1 July 2013 HOC162999.docx","Trafalgar Class Submarines","Trafalgar Class Submarines","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598200/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-10-10","Trafalgar Class Submarines: Decommissioning","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what plans the Government has for the decommissioning of (a) HMS Torbay, (b) HMS Trenchant, (c) HMS Talent and (d) HMS Triumph.","false","Biography information for Steven Paterson","Stirling","Steven Paterson","47777"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598201","Cabinet Office","false","2016-10-19","<p>The Gulf Strategy Integrated Delivery Team was established in 2015.</p><p>Its remit is to coordinate the Government’s strategic approach to UK engagement with the Gulf States as set out in the Strategic Defence and Security Review 2015.</p><p>It employs three full-time and one part-time Government employees. One is military and three are civilian.</p><p>Administration costs were £70,004 in the 2015-16 financial year and the budget for administration costs in the 2016-17 financial year is £423,000. The 2015-16 figure reflects the fact the unit was established later in the financial year.</p>","Ipswich","Ben Gummer","47638 ; 47796 ; 47797","2016-10-19T11:17:58.403Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598201/answer","Biography information for Ben Gummer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598201/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598201/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2016-10-10","Gulf Strategy Unit","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how many (a) military and (b) civilian Government employees have been employed in the Gulf Strategy Unit in each of the last 15 years.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","47725"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598202","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-10-13","<p>JOINT WARRIOR is a bi-annual UK exercise aimed at providing collective maritime-focused training to UK and international navy, air and land forces with invited participation from NATO and other nations. The planning and delivery of this year's exercises involved assets and personnel from the Turkish Armed Forces.</p><p>Turkey has routinely contributed assets and personnel in previous JOINT WARRIOR exercises and this year is no different.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2016-10-13T15:04:07.627Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598202/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598202/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598202/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-10-10","Turkey: Military Exercises","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether the participation of assets of the Turkish armed forces in NATO Operation Joint Warrior 2016 had been planned.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","47803"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598203","Department for International Development","false","2016-10-13","<p>On 21 September, the UK announced an extra £40 million of humanitarian funding to Iraq, taking our total commitment to £90 million this financial year and £169.5 million since June 2014. This new assistance will be targeted specifically to enable a scale up of humanitarian assistance ahead of the Government of Iraq-led Mosul operations. It will include support to efforts aimed at ensuring the protection of civilians, including children.</p><p>The UK will continue to lobby all parties to adhere to International Humanitarian Law and for screening to take place in a transparent manner, under a fully accountable chain of command, and to be monitored independently by the UN and other neutral and impartial humanitarian actors.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2016-10-13T14:50:31.637Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598203/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598203/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598203/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2016-10-10","Iraq: Armed Conflict","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what steps the UK will take to safeguard children and other civilians in any assault on IS in Mosul; what steps she will take to put in place safe routes out for children and families; and if she will ensure that screening procedures take care not to separate families.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","47798"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598204","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-10-17","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the reply given in the House of Lords on 12 September 2016 by my noble Friend the Minister of State for Defence, the right hon. Earl Howe to the noble Lord, Lord West of Spithead to Question HL1533.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2016-10-17T14:25:47.02Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598204/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598204/answer","Hansard Extract  12 September 2016 HL1533.docx","Hansard Extract  12 September 2016 HL1533.docx","Patrol Craft","Patrol Craft","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598204/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-10-10","Patrol Craft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the in-service dates are for the River-Class Offshore Patrol Vessels currently under construction on the Clyde.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","47719"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598205","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-10-17","<p>The discovery of insulating material becoming detached from an avionics cooling line located in a fuel tank is not a design or technical issue, but a sub-contractor quality control issue that affects only a small subset of the 104 operational F-35As in the fleet. The UK is procuring the F-35B variant which is not affected by this issue. UK F-35 Initial Operating Capability is scheduled for December 2018 and remains on track.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2016-10-17T14:33:09.603Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598205/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598205/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598205/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-10-10","Joint Strike Fighter Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what steps his Department is taking to ensure that the insulation on coolant lines in the fuel tanks of UK F35B Lightning II fighters does not suffer decomposition.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","47720"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598206","Ministry of Defence","false","2016-10-17","<table><tbody><tr><td colspan="2" rowspan="5"><p> </p></td><td colspan="6" rowspan="5"><p>UK F-35B simulation trials for Shipborne Rolling Vertical Landing (SRVL) are ongoing. SRVL trials at sea are scheduled to commence as part of the UK's First of Class Flying Trials aboard HMS Queen Elizabeth in late 2018.</p></td></tr></tbody></table>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2016-10-17T14:30:20.507Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598206/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598206/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/598206/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2016-10-10","Joint Strike Fighter Aircraft","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether Royal Air Force F35B Lightning II jets have completed testing for shipborne rolling vertical landing in cooperation with US Air Force and US Navy assets.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","47716"
